asgn1Election

Interface Vote

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Integer>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    VoteList

    public interface Vote
extends java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Integer>

    Interface to specify a collection of Integers representing a vote.

    Vote extends Iterable to allow simple traversal of the entries in the vote. The method Iterable.iterator() must appear in the implementing class.

    Note to students: the guidance below is much stronger than would be given for a real interface. You should assume that the implementing class restricts the vote entries to the number of candidates in an election, and that this is a parameter. The class VoteList must implement this interface. To assist you I have gutted the class but left many signatures in place. It is up to you to complete the task, but you should certainly not expect to see a specification for the constructor of the implementing class, as you have been given here.

    Author:
    hogan

      • addPref

        boolean addPref(int index)

        Method adds the next preference to the vote structure.

        Note that the index given need not be valid - the Vote type may include informal votes, which are detected elsewhere.

        Parameters:
        index - int containing preference to be stored
        Returns:
        boolean status: true if pref added; false if vote already contained numCandidates otherwise
